AMC Networks Seeks $2.23 Billion in Spinoff Loans

-- B y   K r i s t a   G i o v a c c o
-- 
2011-06-08T13:36:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-07/amc-said-to-seek-2-23-billion-of-loans-to-back-spinoff-from-cablevision.html
AMC Networks Inc., the owner and
operator of cable television programming networks, is seeking
$2.23 billion in bank loans to back its spinoff from  Cablevision
Systems Corp. (CVC) , according to two people with knowledge of the
matter.  The JPMorgan Chase & Co.-led transaction includes a $500
million, five-year revolving line of credit, a $1.16 billion,
six year term loan A and a $565 million, 7.5-year term loan B,
said the people, who declined to be identified because the terms
are private.  The New York-based company will meet with lenders June 9 at
1 p.m. in  New York , one of the people said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krista Giovacco in New York at 
 kgiovacco1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Faris Khan at 
 fkhan33@bloomberg.net . 